-- Bank of America to invest $2 bln in Countrywide: WSJ
-- 
-- Wed Aug 22, 2007 6:15pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/08/22/us-countrywide-bankamerica-idUSN2218820920070822

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Bank of America Corp, the No. 2 U.S. bank, plans to invest $2 billion in preferred stock issued by Countrywide Financial Corp, the mortgage lender that has faced a liquidity crunch recently, the Wall Street Journal reported on Wednesday. 

 Countrywide shares were up 19 percent in after-hours trading on the report. (Reporting by  Christian Plumb )